cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes a new feature-based, model-free, object-aware dynamic SLAM algorithm that is designed for autonomous systems operating in unstructured dynamic environments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics sub-category.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The proposed algorithm exploits semantic segmentation to estimate the motion of rigid objects in a scene. This indicates that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision sub-category.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The algorithm is model-free and uses semantic segmentation to identify moving objects in a scene. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning sub-category.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed algorithm is able to estimate the motion of rigid objects in a scene without the need to estimate their poses or have any prior knowledge of their 3D models. This indicates that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence sub-category.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a new algorithm for simultaneous localisation and mapping (SLAM) that is designed for autonomous systems operating in unstructured dynamic environments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Systems and Control sub-category.
